message.content:
To determine the average number of cereal bits used per design, we can divide the total number of cereal bits (63) by the number of designs created (9). 

Average number of cereal bits per design = Total number of cereal bits / Number of designs
                                     = 63 / 9
                                     = 7

So, on average, Emily used about 7 cereal bits in each design. It is not possible to determine if she used an equal number of cereal bits in each design without further information.
